Netflix has confirmed another season of South African hit series Blood and Water. JOHANNESBURG - Netflix South Africa has announced that local series Blood and Water has been renewed for a second season. The exciting news was made by the show’s director Nosipho Dumisa in a video posted on social media on Monday. READ: Mmabatho Montsho's film wins international award Season 1 of the hit series follows Puleng - played by Ama Qamata as she tries to solve the mystery of her sister who was kidnapped as a baby. The series also stars Gail Mabalane, Arno Greeff, Natasha Thahane, Cindy Mahlangu, and Thabang Molaba.